Support Vector Machine (SVM) Classification
Project Overview

This project implements a Support Vector Machine (SVM) classifier to predict whether a breast tumor is malignant or benign using the Breast Cancer Wisconsin Dataset. SVM is a supervised machine learning algorithm widely used for classification tasks due to its effectiveness in handling high-dimensional data.

Dataset

Dataset Name: Breast Cancer Wisconsin Dataset

Source: Scikit-Learn Built-in Dataset

Dataset Description

The dataset contains features computed from digitized images of breast mass cell nuclei.

Total Samples: 569
Features: 30 numerical features
Classes:
Malignant (0)
Benign (1)
Feature Examples
Mean Radius
Mean Texture
Mean Perimeter
Mean Area
Mean Smoothness
Technologies Used
Python
Scikit-Learn
NumPy
Algorithm

Support Vector Machine (SVM)

Evaluation Metrics
Accuracy Score
Classification Report
Precision
Recall
F1-Score
Expected Outcome

The model classifies breast tumors with high accuracy and demonstrates the effectiveness of SVM in binary classification tasks.
